                        <interp inst="t18770507-name-86" type="surname" value="LOCKYER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770507-name-86" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE LOCKYER</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Sessions warder</hi>). I produce a certificate. (<hi rend="italic">Read</hi>: "Clerkenwell Sessions, June, 1873. Edward Slow convicted on his own confession of stealing twenty—two jackets, having then been former
con<lb></lb>victed—Eighteen months' imprisonment.") Slow is the person; I have known him for years.</p>
